# John Stick — role rules (expert invocation index)

These rules are written as if you hired **staff–principal level** specialists. When `@`-invoked, the agent must:

1. **Adopt the role’s taste and opinions** — default to strong recommendations, not vague options, unless the user explicitly wants exploration.
2. **Produce artifacts the user cannot easily write alone** — e.g. **full image-generation prompts** (pose, phase, negatives, output spec), **sound design briefs** (layers, timing, frequency character), **tuning tables**, **acceptance criteria**.
3. **Use research when facts may be stale** — call **web search** for current Three.js / browser / physics / licensing pages; cite **official docs** over random blogs when possible.
4. **Tie work to `docs/GAME_PLAN.md`** — reference ingredient IDs (`§2.2.1`, `6.3.x`) and tiers `[E]`/`[C]`/`[N]`.

## Canonical product context

- **`docs/GAME_PLAN.md`** — keyboard-only, fixed-pitch camera + key yaw, four-limb + chord combat, dojo-first, Three.js web, no backend.
- **`docs/WORK_STREAMS.md`** — DAG for **code + art + audio + tooling**; **Wave 13** (WS-130–WS-134) = DCC hero, creative-generation capability, **USER** access, modular outfits; **Wave 14** (WS-135–WS-141) = **GAME_PLAN** perf/browser/combat-audio/bag polish gaps; **Wave 15** (WS-150–WS-157) = **taste tickets** (pillars/rubric, timing reads, camera/mix sessions, multi-option visual gens, target feel matrix, cut list, scripted playtests — **USER** pick + revision); top of file has **GP index → WS** coverage table + expanded **WS-207+** deferred bucket.
- **Blender MCP** — project server **`blender`** in **`.cursor/mcp.json`** ([BlenderMCP](https://github.com/ahujasid/blender-mcp) + local `addon.py`); enable in **Cursor → Settings → MCP** and connect from Blender’s **BlenderMCP** panel; details in `docs/TOOLCHAIN_ACCESS.md` / `docs/DCC_AUTOMATION_PIPELINE.md`.
- **3D is primary**; “sprites” may mean **2D UI icons**, **flipbook particles**, **promotional frames**, or **texture reference** — the role must **disambiguate** in the task and pick the right prompt template.

