Task: <goal or GAME_PLAN id e.g. 2.2.1 chord system>
Deliverable: <prompt pack | sound brief | code | doc | review>
Constraints: <tier, no mouse, no backend, deadline>
Refs: <files, links, screenshots>
```

## Shared: image prompt skeleton (creative roles adapt this)

When generating **any** visual prompt for John Stick, include **all** applicable lines:

- **Subject:** stick figure / limb-readable silhouette / which limb leads.
- **Action phase:** windup | peak impact | follow-through | recovery (one frame family per prompt).
- **Style:** stylized 3D OR 2D cel/vector (pick one); **no photoreal flesh**.
- **Camera:** orthographic side / ¾ / isometric; **fixed**; match game readability.
- **Background:** flat color hex or transparent; **no watermark/text**.
- **Output:** resolution, PNG/WebP, alpha if UI; **sprite sheet** = grid N×M, cell WxH, consistent padding.
- **Negative:** extra limbs, motion blur smear, gore (unless `[N]` blood tier approved), busy backgrounds, logos.
- **Consistency:** repeat **same** style tokens across a set (e.g. “thick black outline, round joints, warm rim light”).

## Shared: sound brief skeleton (audio + any role requesting SFX)

- **Event id:** `sfx_<context>_<move>_<tier>_##`
- **Duration:** ms; **one-shot** vs **loop**
- **Transient:** click/snap character (freq range, brightness)
- **Body:** thud/slam weight (pitch, decay)
- **Sweetener:** whoosh / bass drop / debris (stereo width)
- **Context:** dojo room vs outdoor (reverb note)
- **Loudness:** target relative to `sfx_ui_confirm`
- **Variation:** pitch ± cents, N alternates
- **Implementation:** bus (SFX/Combat/UI), polyphony cap
